NeoNet app

Created by Thomas Huet, Niccolo Mazzucco, Miriam Cubas Morera, Juan Gibaja, and F. Xavier Oms

A RShiny app for mapping radiocarbon dates (C14) from Late Mesolithic/Early Neolithic transition in the North Central-Western Mediterranean watershed. The stable version of the NeoNet app and the web tutorial are hosted on the University of Pisa Shiny Server.

The NeoNet app offers a geographical window provided by the Leaflet package used for selection of radiocarbon dates by location, by chronology, and by quality of dates.

Once selected, the radiocarbon dates can be calibrated on-the-fly, separately or grouped by layers, sites, periods, and the seriated summed probability densities (SPD) plots of these dates can be downloaded.

To go further on the development version of the app, you can check the contribution rules and the relevant license

The development version of the app is in the R/ folder
